ext to no one visits your site to check out the design. They want information or are trying to complete some action. If they are not noticing the design, it means it is not getting in their way and conforms to the content. As long as everything is intuitive and the content is easy to find and consume, the look and feel is secondary at best. You could layout the content to make it look like a text file with a menu and search, and no one would care if they can easily get what they came for. Boring yes, but it remains functional and fulfills its purpose. Have you ever paid any attention to the design of Google\'s main page and search results? Or have you seldom noticed it? I\'ll agree that the UI in some Google products is not the best, but their main line - search - is excellent even though it looks boring. I\'ll bet that you use it everyday despite this. And you know why? because it functions exceptionally well, my grandma can use it like a pro, and it gives you what you want. It\'s the very reason Google rose to mind blowing success nearly overnight.\r\n\r\nI\'m not trying to piss anybody off, albeit a reality check could benefit some. Design is hard and important, but becomes counter-productive if your number one concern is not the user. No one wants a site that looks boring, humans appreciate visual appeal. The best work comes when great designers and developers work together at each step of the process and can dish and receive criticism to push each discipline to its limits. If you need a safe zone to shelter from this, you are in the wrong industry.\r\n\r\nI\'m not on your website to appreciate art. Don\'t overload my senses please.','Let\'s talk about Creative','','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-12-24 08:03:05','2017-12-24 08:03:05','',6,'http://derulski.local/?p=31',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2017-12-24 08:04:21','2017-12-24 08:04:21','Grab a dictionary. look up \'creative.\'\r\n\r\n\"relating to or involving the imagination or origin